<subSubSection pageId="557" pageNumber="558" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="557.[810,1452,955,2070]" pageId="557" pageNumber="558">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,992,1908,1934]" pageId="557" pageNumber="558">Etymology</emphasis>
. The generic name is from the Greek 
<emphasis box="[810,863,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="557" pageNumber="558">scoli</emphasis>
(=curved, crooked) and 
<emphasis box="[1168,1227,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="557" pageNumber="558">soma</emphasis>
(=body), referring the curved body of the adult female in species of the new genus. Gender neuter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="559" lastPageNumber="560" pageId="557" pageNumber="558" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="557.[810,1452,955,2070]" lastBlockId="559.[136,778,1159,1730]" lastPageId="559" lastPageNumber="560" pageId="557" pageNumber="558">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,972,2044,2070]" pageId="557" pageNumber="558">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[981,1110,2044,2070]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scoliosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="557" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen.nov.">
<emphasis box="[981,1110,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="557" pageNumber="558">Scoliosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1113,1215,2044,2070]" pageId="557" pageNumber="558" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1113,1208,2044,2070]" pageId="557" pageNumber="558">gen.nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1332,1452,2044,2070]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Gallincola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="557" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1332,1452,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="557" pageNumber="558">Gallincola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[136,245,1159,1186]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,238,1159,1185]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
: they have a similar body form and both have a strong distal tooth on the mandibular gnathobase. Interestingly, both live in galls in solitary ascidians. However, the cephalic appendages of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[587,716,1261,1287]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scoliosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[587,716,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">Scoliosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are much more simplified than in 
<taxonomicName authority="The" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[598,718,1295,1321]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Gallincola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[598,718,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">Gallincola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
The mandibular exopod is armed with 5 setae in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[136,256,1363,1389]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Gallincola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[136,256,1363,1389]" italics="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">Gallincola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[263,370,1363,1390]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[263,364,1363,1389]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
but with 4 setae in 
<taxonomicName authority="The" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[592,721,1363,1389]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scoliosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[592,721,1363,1389]" italics="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">Scoliosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
The maxillule of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[383,503,1397,1423]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Gallincola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[383,503,1397,1423]" italics="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">Gallincola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[509,615,1398,1424]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[509,608,1398,1424]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
bears as many as 9 setae on the arthrite and has a biramous palp but this appendage in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[295,424,1465,1491]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scoliosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[295,424,1465,1491]" italics="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">Scoliosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[432,540,1466,1492]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[432,534,1466,1492]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
bears a total of only 5 setae on the arthrite and has a rudimentary, lobate palp. Othernotable differences include: in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[540,669,1533,1559]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scoliosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[540,669,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">Scoliosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[674,778,1534,1560]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[674,771,1534,1560]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
the urosome is 5-segmented compared to 4-segmented in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[136,256,1601,1627]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Gallincola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[136,256,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">Gallincola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[269,380,1602,1628]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[269,374,1602,1628]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the antennule is broad, leaf-like compared to elongate in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[431,551,1635,1661]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Gallincola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[431,551,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">Gallincola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[562,672,1636,1662]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[562,667,1636,1662]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and the maxillary syncoxa has only 2 endites compared with 3 endites in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[251,371,1703,1729]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Gallincola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[251,371,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">Gallincola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[378,484,1704,1730]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[378,478,1704,1730]" pageId="559" pageNumber="560">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
